I'm pretty happy with where I am, I think I'm doing pretty well for level 42.  What I noticed recently though is that when I upgraded to the old dwarven cultural and got a decent AC jump (about 50 to 60 points from where I was) there seemed to be a decent difference in the damage I took.  I was thrilled to recently break 2k at level 42 unbuffed, but I'm wondering if I should trade some of that to push my AC up as far as I can.<br>
<br>
Are there any reasonable HP for AC trade offs that jump out at anyone?  Obviously, I want to keep my health as high as I can, but I'm thinking that a 1k/1.5k ratio is probably better for me than a 2k/800.<br>
<br>
